{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 5.\tx360\tab Hit Record in REAPER to capture MIDI output\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Modes:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8226 ? Automatic: Continuous playback (use Play/Stop buttons) \u8226 ? MIDI Trigger: Playback follows your MIDI keyboard input\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li1440 \fi0 Select MIDI device from dropdown first\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Features:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8226 ? Per-voice controls: Note, Velocity, Sustain %, Rate \u8226 ? Real-time transpose (overridden in MIDI Trigger mode)\line \u8226 ? BPM sync with project tempo \u8226 ? Randomization with individual toggles \u8226 ? Save and Load presets (also remembers settings per project)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Notes:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Track must remain armed during playback. Edit 'VOICE_COUNT' variable below if you want more than 8 voices. Warning: untested.\par}
