{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Render Marker Sections Within Timeline Selection\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab 1.\tx360\tab Finds all normal markers in the current time selection.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab 2.\tx360\tab Prompts user to open Render Settings and save them (bounding=Project regions, filename=$region, etc.).\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab 3.\tx360\tab Upon confirmation, creates a region for each chunk from marker i to marker i+1 (or sel_end if it\u8217's the last marker).\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab 4.\tx360\tab Calls "Render project, using the most recent render settings" (which the user just saved).\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab 5.\tx360\tab Deletes the newly-created regions, leaving your project as it was.\sa180\sa180\par}
}

