{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Space SFX Variations by Markers\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Make a timeline selection of a set of markers where SFX variations may be overlapping (e.g. when producing foley)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Each marker inside the selection is considered a variation start.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Items belong to a variation if their START is inside that variation's boundary i.e. before the next marker.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The last variation's right boundary = max end among all items that overlap the time selection.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Keeps the first variation anchored. For each next variation, inserts empty space defined by user padding value.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Rest of the project is pushed rightward relative to the amount of time added by the script operation.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Regions created for each variation for easy rendering. Naming based off user provided input (default 'SFX)\sa180\par}
}

