{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Toggle: Auto Track Renamer\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 While enabled, continuously renames tracks using names of media items contained within.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Track naming is based on the following rules:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Parent track has no media items: 'TRACK_EMPTY'\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab If parent track or any of its children has media items:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab If any media item is a video file (.mp4, .mov, etc), base name is "!REF_VISUAL".\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Else gathers all words within media items on the track; any media items on parent track have word priority.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Two most frequent words become the base name for the parent track.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab All children/sub-children are named numerically sequentially.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Empty Item override:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab If ANY track has an Empty Item with text, that track becomes its own base group:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab That track's name is the Empty Item text (uppercased), with no numeric suffix.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Its children inherit that base and are numbered in sequentially.\sa180\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 TIPS : -> Use '!' ahead of the track name to lock it from being renamed by the script. -> Use the variables below 'ignore_words' and 'prefer_words' to tailer the naming preferences to your liking.\par}
}

